---
title: Chicken & Kale Fall Harvest Salad with Walnuts & Cranberry-Maple Dijon Dressing
description: Cooler weather always makes us think about…salad! Seriously, this robust salad will give you all the cozy fall feels. We toss tender kale with roasted Brussels sprouts and delicata squash, chewy dried cranberries, and a creamy, tangy honey Dijon dressing. It’s all topped with Parmesan cheese and walnuts for a hearty-yet-light-feeling dinner you’re going to want to make all year round.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6321d93b73605bea4f05974c-d369b5ad.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/chicken-kale-fall-harvest-salad-6321d93b73605bea4f05974c-31426c7b.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chicken-kale-fall-harvest-salad-6321d93b73605bea4f05974c
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 820 kcal
  fat: 42 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 83 g
  sugar: 43 g
  protein: 45 g
  fiber: 13 g
  sodium: 530 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise (quarter any larger sprouts). Halve @Delicata Squash{1} lengthwise; scoop out seeds with a #spoon{} and discard. Slice crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Remove and discard any large stems from @Kale{4%ounce}; chop into bite-size pieces. Halve @Lemon{1}.

Toss Brussels sprouts and squash on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%teaspoon} and a big pinch of @Salt{pinch} and @Pepper{pinch}. (For 4 servings, divide between 2 sheets; roast on top and middle racks.) Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Let cool at least ~{5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add kale and a drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon} to a #large bowl{}; using your hands, massage until leaves are tender, ~{30-60%seconds}.

> Don't skip this step—massaging helps make kale's texture more salad-friendly.

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @Dried Cranberries{1%ounce}, 1 TBSP water (2 TBSP for 4 servings), and juice from lemon. Cover with #plastic wrap{}; microwave until softened, ~{1%minute}. Transfer cranberries to a #plate{}, reserving lemon juice mixture in bowl.

To bowl with lemon juice mixture, add @Dijon Mustard{4%teaspoon}, @Maple Syrup{2%tablespoon}, @Olive Oil{3%tablespoon} (6 TBSP for 4), and @Sugar{1/4%teaspoon} (½ tsp for 4). Whisk to combine. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

To bowl with kale, add roasted veggies, drained cranberries, half the Dijon dressing, and half the @Parmesan Cheese{3%tablespoon}. Gently toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide salad between plates or shallow bowls. Drizzle with remaining Dijon dressing; garnish with @Walnuts{1/2%ounce} and remaining Parmesan. Serve.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise; serve atop salad.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.